<br>
Anyway, what I'm looking for here is an adult discussion.. you see this summer I've gotten another job, I guess.. I'm kind of working as a nurse.<br>
<br>
I work with retarded people who can more or less take care of them selves, they need help with medication and food, the rest they do themselves (they have apartments of their own and all that).<br>
<br>
One of the girls there has a perfectly clear mind, ie. she's not retarded mentally. But, her brain can not control her bodyfunctions properly, as in she can't talk, she can't write, she can't see properly and most of all she can't move and do stuff with her hands properly. <br>
<br>
My point with all this is that this girl, has a mind that functions perfectly, she understands two languages (Swedish and English) since she is originally from America. She hears people talking about her in third person all day long, she knows that she's retarded, she knows that she can't do what everyone else does. Can you imagine how crappy she must feel? I highly doubt she's really a happy person.<br>
<br>
Now for my second point in this babbling, as I've been working there I've been thinking.. if I through some weird way ever end up having children, what if I got a retarded child? What the hell would I do? Most of the patients there have perfectly healthy brothers and sisters mind you. My answer to my own question is rather.. cruel I guess, I'd prolly kill myself and the child if it was ever to happen.<br>
<br>
What would you do? <p><html><TABLE><TD valign=top><IMG SRC="http://user.tninet.se/~mhf993y/anna/sig.jpg"></TD>
